        <section name="Introduction">
            <p>This Java-based converter reads popular peak-list formats and
                transforms them into the M/Z data XML format. Where
                necessary (i.e. the source does not provide this information)
                the user is presented a form to fill in additional
                information required by the M/Z data XML format. There is also
                a
                <a href="schemadoc/mzdata.xsd.html">schema documentation</a>
                available.
            </p>
            <p>There is a Swing-based GUI available and a Struts-based
                web-application in planning. The following input formats
                are planned to be supported:</p>
            <table>
                <tr>
                    <th>Format</th>
                    <th>Implemented</th>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>DTA (Thermo Finnigan)</td>
